  <span class="nl">background-repeat</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="nb">repeat-x</span><span class="p">;</span>
  <span class="nl">text-shadow</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="m">1px</span> <span class="m">1px</span> <span class="m">0px</span> <span class="no">white</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="m">-1px</span> <span class="m">1px</span> <span class="m">0px</span> <span class="no">white</span> <span class="p">;</span>
  <span class="p">}</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Like most hacky CSS fixes, itâ€™s not really <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fire-and-forget">fire and forget</a>. Youâ€™ll probably have to counteract its effects in some other declarations.</p>

<p>A few tips: Itâ€™s span level, so if you wrap an anchor tag around a block of items it wonâ€™t work properly. You also have to apply the mixin for a hover state. The text shadow is white, so if you use it over a color background, it may cause issues.</p>

<p>It also doesnâ€™t work in â€“ wait for it  â€“ IE8 or &lt;, so youâ€™ll have to fall back to the browser default. But then again, people who still use IE8 donâ€™t deserve nice things anyway.</p>

